
// This Hyperlambda code sends a SignalR message to a specified session, indicating an error condition. The message includes an error flag set to true, a status code of 500, and a descriptive message advising to configure the type for more function invocations or to change the prompt. The [sockets.signal] slot is used to transmit these arguments as a JSON object to the subscribers of the session. The [args] node contains the details of the error message being sent.
sockets.signal:x:@.session
   args
      error:bool:true
      status:int:500
      message:Too many function invocations. Configure your type to handle more invocations or change your prompt.
